  <section class="container">
    <h1>Basics of Practice</h1>
    <p class="lead">Daily practice consists of chanting <em>Nam-Myoho-Renge-Kyo</em> and reciting from the Lotus Sutra (Gongyo) before the Gohonzon. We also share Buddhism with others and study to deepen understanding.</p>

    <div class="grid kv">
      <div><h3>Chanting</h3><p>Begin by chanting <em>Nam-Myoho-Renge-Kyo</em> with sincerity. Even a few minutes daily plants the seed for profound change.</p></div>
      <div><h3>Gongyo</h3><p>Recitation from the Lotus Sutra is performed morning and evening. Visit the temple to learn how.</p></div>
      <div><h3>Gohonzon</h3><p>The Gohonzon embodies the enlightened life of the True Buddha. We practice to fuse our lives with this Law.</p></div>
      <div><h3>Practice for Others</h3><p>Sharing Buddhism is essential—helping others awaken their Buddha nature.</p></div>
    </div>

    <p><a class="cta" href="plan-visit.html#intro">Attend an Introductory Meeting</a></p>
